17/01/2003
THESSALONIKI, Greece -- A two-day summit of Southeast European police officers begins in Thessaloniki on Saturday (18 January). 
Officials say participants are going to discuss more effective co-operation in preventing organised crime, human trafficking, and drug trafficking. 
This is the second meeting of this sort; Greece wants it to become standard procedure. 
(Macedonian Press Agency - 16/01/03)
